---
import Base from '~/layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Terms of service" description="The terms under which Kai is provided.">
  <article class="legal">
    <h1>Terms of service</h1>
    <p><strong>Phase 0 placeholder.</strong> This page is a skeleton — the
    real terms live in the deployment overlay
    (<code>swarm-cloud</code>) and need legal sign-off before the public
    SaaS opens for business.</p>

    <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>You're responsible for what you do with your workspace.</li>
      <li>No illegal content, no abuse of others, no attempts to break the platform.</li>
      <li>Free-tier abuse (mass signups, scripted requests) is grounds for suspension.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Service availability</h2>
    <p>The free tier ships best-effort. Paid tiers carry SLA targets that
    arrive with the v1 production launch.</p>

    <h2>Pricing changes</h2>
    <p>30-day notice for any price change on existing subscriptions; new
    signups always see current pricing.</p>

    <h2>Termination</h2>
    <p>You can cancel any time. We can suspend accounts that violate the
    acceptable-use policy. Data deletion follows the <a href="/privacy">privacy
    policy</a>.</p>
  </article>
</Base>
